<div id="review_2974732708" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2974732708" />
    <a title="Petra is like a jigsaw fragmented &amp; pieces missing" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1237196-petra-is-like-a-jigsaw-fragmented-pieces-missing"><img alt="Petra is like a jigsaw fragmented &amp; pieces missing" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1642342196p2/1237196.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2974732708?book_show_action=true">Sep 12, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Petra is like a jigsaw fragmented &amp; pieces missing" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Petra is like a jigsaw fragmented &amp; pieces missing" href="/user/show/1237196-petra-is-like-a-jigsaw-fragmented-pieces-missing">Petra is like a jigsaw fragmented &amp; pieces missing</a>
      </span>

          added it




        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1237196-petra-is-like-a-jigsaw-fragmented-pieces-missing?shelf=1-awaiting-review-but-read">1-awaiting-review-but-read</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2974732708" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16285977525641603715">1. The Nun - an explication of the very interesting Jain religion and the Jain view of the world and the world to come. It is older and more &apos;pure&apos; than Hinduism or Buddhism, both of which it has elements of. <br/><br/>So far, this book is fascinating and beautifully, lyrically written. But lyrical in the sense of descriptive in a way that paints a picture. Not lyrical in the sense of pretty rainbows, floating clouds and redundant rubbish like that. </span>
  <span id="freeText16285977525641603715" style="display:none">1. The Nun - an explication of the very interesting Jain religion and the Jain view of the world and the world to come. It is older and more 'pure' than Hinduism or Buddhism, both of which it has elements of. <br /><br />So far, this book is fascinating and beautifully, lyrically written. But lyrical in the sense of descriptive in a way that paints a picture. Not lyrical in the sense of pretty rainbows, floating clouds and redundant rubbish like that. </span>
  <a data-text-id="16285977525641603715" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
