<div id="review_97088310" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/97088310" />
    <a title="Ram" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1630537-ram"><img alt="Ram" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1224265147p2/1630537.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/97088310?book_show_action=true">Apr 04, 2010</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ram" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ram" href="/user/show/1630537-ram">Ram</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer97088310" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16174143966847807157">As an Indian in India, I have always read with interest the writings of foreigners about India. The earlier books of Dalrymple appeared to me to be delivering a well researched and authenticated version of his views about aspects of India. More and more I find him cashing in on his established reputation merely to sell his latest volume.<br/> A disappointment - even the proof reading seems to have been hurried as an example note &quot;... Jacobean aristocrat clad in breaches ... &quot;!!</span>
  <span id="freeText16174143966847807157" style="display:none">As an Indian in India, I have always read with interest the writings of foreigners about India. The earlier books of Dalrymple appeared to me to be delivering a well researched and authenticated version of his views about aspects of India. More and more I find him cashing in on his established reputation merely to sell his latest volume.<br /> A disappointment - even the proof reading seems to have been hurried as an example note "... Jacobean aristocrat clad in breaches ... "!!</span>
  <a data-text-id="16174143966847807157" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

<tr class="no_border feedFooterReview" id="update_comment_stuff_Review97088310">
  <td colspan="2">
    <div class="updateActionLinks">
        <a class="right flag" rel="nofollow" id="flag_link97088310" title="Flag this review as inappropriate." href="/flagged/new?resource_id=97088310&amp;resource_type=Review&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F6943146-nine-lives">flag</a>





